Sentence: The sun shines brightly.
The : definite article, singular, determiner for "sun"
sun : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "shines"
shines : verb "shine", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice
brightly : adverb, modifies the verb "shines"

Sentence: She reads a book.
She : personal pronoun, third person singular, feminine, subject of the verb "reads"
reads : verb "read", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice
a : indefinite article, singular, determiner for "book"
book : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "reads"

Sentence: London feels cold today.
London : proper noun, singular, subject of the verb "feels"
feels : verb "feel", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice, linking verb
cold : adjective, singular, subject complement describing "London"
today : adverb of time, modifies the verb "feels"

Sentence: Dogs bark loudly at night.
Dogs : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "bark"
bark : verb "bark", third person plural, simple present tense, active voice
loudly : adverb, modifies the verb "bark"
at : preposition, introduces the prepositional phrase "at night"
night : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: He is a doctor.
He : personal pronoun, third person singular, masculine, subject of the verb "is"
is : verb "be", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice, linking verb
a : indefinite article, singular, determiner for "doctor"
doctor : common noun, singular, subject complement identifying "He"

Sentence: Water boils at 100 degrees.
Water : common noun, singular, uncountable, subject of the verb "boils"
boils : verb "boil", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice
at : preposition, introduces the prepositional phrase "at 100 degrees"
100 : numeral, modifies "degrees"
degrees : common noun, plural, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: Maria sings beautifully.
Maria : proper noun, singular, subject of the verb "sings"
sings : verb "sing", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice
beautifully : adverb, modifies the verb "sings"

Sentence: They live in Paris.
They : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "live"
live : verb "live", third person plural, simple present tense, active voice
in : preposition, introduces the prepositional phrase "in Paris"
Paris : proper noun, singular, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: The sky turns gray before rain.
The : definite article, singular, determiner for "sky"
sky : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "turns"
turns : verb "turn", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice, linking verb
gray : adjective, singular, subject complement describing "sky"
before : preposition, introduces the prepositional phrase "before rain"
rain : common noun, singular, uncountable, object of the preposition "before"

Sentence: Birds fly south for winter.
Birds : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "fly"
fly : verb "fly", third person plural, simple present tense, active voice
south : adverb of direction, modifies the verb "fly"
for : preposition, introduces the prepositional phrase "for winter"
