Sentence: My brother works hard.
My : possessive adjective, first person singular, determiner for "brother"
brother : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "works"
works : verb "work", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice
hard : adverb, modifies the verb "works"

Sentence: The soup tastes salty.
The : definite article, singular, determiner for "soup"
soup : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "tastes"
tastes : verb "taste", third person singular, simple present tense, active voice, linking verb
